<dl id="n22085a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22085a">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22085a"> 85(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> impetum</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Bruno received an impetus towards the study of Aristotle in the original works, if not also in the original tongue, which stood him in admirable stead when he came later to attack the foundations of the vulgar philosophy. <small> J. Lewis McIntyre, <a name="BRUNO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BRUNO"><cite title="source">Giordano Bruno</cite></a> (1903) (?)121</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
